  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Peacebuilding and Durable Solutions in Sudan Through Early Recovery and Nexus Interventions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute to Sudan HRP 2020 Strategic Objective 2 &#x201C;Contribute to building resilience to recurrent shocks and improving vulnerable people&#x2019;s access to basic services; protecting assets; contributing to durable solutions; integrating early recovery and rebuild livelihoods; reducing needs, risks and vulnerabilities with a longer-term view; building or rebuilding systems, assets and local capacities; enhancing early warning systems; chronic malnutrition&#x201D;. The overall objective of this intervention is to contribute towards creating a conducive environment for durable solutions for Sudanese IDPs, returnees (including IDPs and Refugees), and host communities, through quick impact livelihoods interventions and promoting and supporting &#x2018;instant&#x2019; community-based peacebuilding and social cohesion in seven selected states. Output 1: Co-existence and peace is fostered with a specific focus to land related conflicts that prevent Durable Solutions in Darfur, Blue Nile and South Kordofan. Output 2: Community peace and social cohesion enhanced to facilitate durable solutions. Output 3: Women and Youth Resilience to extreme vulnerability strengthened. Output 4: Community Productive capacities and emergency income-generation opportunities for vulnerable conflict-affected communities restored. This project directly targets 126,304 people with Early Recovery engagements and 84,203 people with Food Security - Agriculture engagements.</narrative>
  </description>
